sequenceDiagram
    title SD-03: Anomaly Detection & Audit Report Generation

    actor Auditor
    participant AuditAPI as Audit API (/api/audit)
    participant AnomalyDet as Anomaly Detector
    participant AuditSvc as Audit Service
    participant DB as Database
    participant ReportGen as Report Generator

    Note over AnomalyDet,DB: Continuous background anomaly monitoring

    AnomalyDet->>DB: Fetch recent task records
    DB-->>AnomalyDet: Return task feature vectors
    AnomalyDet->>AnomalyDet: Run Isolation Forest scoring
    AnomalyDet->>AnomalyDet: Run One-Class SVM scoring
    AnomalyDet->>AnomalyDet: Ensemble score > threshold (0.75)?

    alt Anomaly Detected
        AnomalyDet->>DB: UPDATE task risk_level=CRITICAL
        AnomalyDet->>AuditSvc: Log ANOMALY_DETECTED event
        AuditSvc->>DB: INSERT audit_log
        AnomalyDet->>AuditSvc: Trigger escalation notification
    end

    Note over Auditor,DB: Auditor requests compliance report

    Auditor->>AuditAPI: GET /api/audit/logs?date_range=today
    AuditAPI->>DB: Query audit_logs with filters
    DB-->>AuditAPI: Return filtered audit records
    AuditAPI-->>Auditor: 200 OK {audit_logs: [...]}

    Auditor->>AuditAPI: POST /api/audit/report/generate
    AuditAPI->>AuditSvc: generate_compliance_report()
    AuditSvc->>DB: Aggregate task stats by status, risk, agent
    DB-->>AuditSvc: Return aggregated data
    AuditSvc->>ReportGen: Build report {tasks, violations, agents}
    ReportGen->>ReportGen: Format report data
    ReportGen-->>AuditSvc: Report object
    AuditSvc->>DB: INSERT audit_log (REPORT_GENERATED)
    AuditSvc-->>AuditAPI: Report ready
    AuditAPI-->>Auditor: 200 OK {report_id, report_data, date}
